## Product Search Endpoint — Typesense Integration

### 1. Install the Typesense client

```bash
npm install typesense
# or
pip install typesense
```

---

### 2. Initialize the client

```typescript
import Typesense from 'typesense';

const client = new Typesense.Client({
  nodes: [{ host: 'your-typesense-host', port: 443, protocol: 'https' }],
  apiKey: process.env.TYPESENSE_API_KEY,
  connectionTimeoutSeconds: 5,
});
```

---

### 3. Define the search endpoint

```typescript
// POST /api/products/search
app.get('/api/products/search', async (req, res) => {
  const { q, lat, lng, radius_km, page = 1, per_page = 20 } = req.query;

  const searchParams: any = {
    q: q || '*',
    query_by: 'name,description,category',
    num_typos: 2,              // leverage typo-tolerant ranking
    page: Number(page),
    per_page: Number(per_page),
    sort_by: '_text_match:desc',
  };

  // Geo-spatial filter — only applied when coordinates are provided
  if (lat && lng) {
    searchParams.filter_by =
      `location:(${lat}, ${lng}, ${radius_km ?? 50} km)`;
    searchParams.sort_by =
      `location(${lat}, ${lng}):asc,_text_match:desc`;
  }

  try {
    const results = await client
      .collections('products')
      .documents()
      .search(searchParams);

    res.json({
      hits: results.hits?.map(h => h.document),
      total: results.found,
      page: results.page,
    });
  } catch (err) {
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Search failed', detail: err.message });
  }
});
```

---

### 4. Make sure your collection schema includes the geo field

```typescript
await client.collections().create({
  name: 'products',
  fields: [
    { name: 'name',        type: 'string' },
    { name: 'description', type: 'string' },
    { name: 'category',    type: 'string', facet: true },
    { name: 'price',       type: 'float' },
    { name: 'location',    type: 'geopoint' },   // required for geo filters
  ],
  default_sorting_field: 'price',
});
```

---

### Key things wired in

| Feature | How it's used |
|---|---|
| **Typo tolerance** | `num_typos: 2` on `query_by` fields |
| **Geo-spatial filter** | `filter_by: location:(lat, lng, radius km)` |
| **Geo-aware ranking** | `sort_by` blends distance + text match when coords are present |

